parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key takes a long time to eject from the ignition switch
the key becomes stuck in the ignition
the vehicle fails to turn off
the ABS and engine warning indicators illuminate continuously
and the ignition switch seizes in the "on" position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, such as fire hazards, loss of power, and malfunctioning of essential systems like headlights, wipers, and locks.
symptoms: Rear light sockets melting and smoking
gauges stopping working
wipers
lights
and power locks malfunctioning
daytime running lights flickering
and service engine light coming on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses complete power
stalls
or has difficulty shifting gears
and the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the body and paint can cause rust and corrosion, leading to structural damage and safety issues.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the body
peeling paint
and broken trunk and moon roof.

symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy

the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle stalls without warning
the ABS light comes on

the vehicle skids or loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to lock up or become loose, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering wheel can cause the outer cover and foam to separate from the inner steel frame, leading to loss of ability to steer the car, which can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel outer cover and foam separate from the inner steel frame

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioner and electrical systems can cause loud noises, rattling, and popping sounds, which can be distracting and lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The air conditioner makes a loud noise

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear of the brakes can cause the rotors and other brake components to fail, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The brakes squeal and make a grinding noise

symptoms: The vehicle loses power

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Front end noise can be a sign of underlying issues, such as worn or loose components, which can lead to loss of control or accidents.
